---++ Register, unsubscribe and view lists
To subscribe to a list, send an email to listserv@fnal.gov with subscribe listname firstname lastname in the body of the email. For example, if John Smith wanted to subscribe to OSG-General, he would send an email that looked like this:

&lt;pre class=&quot;screen&quot;&gt;To : listserv@fnal.gov
Subject : (can be left blank)
----- Message Text -----
subscribe OSG-General John Smith 
&lt;/pre&gt;

To unsubscribe from a list, send an email to listserv@fnal.gov with signoff listname in the body of the email. For example, to unsubscribe from OSG-Int, one would use the command &quot;signoff OSG-INT&quot; in the body of the message.

To find out information about a list send email to listserv@fnal.gov with &quot;review xxx&quot;  (without &quot;) where xxx is the listname as the body.

[[http://listserv.fnal.gov/archives/][Here]] is an achive of all mailing lists at Fermilab. To view a !ListServ archive with all the messages in a list, go to =http://listserv.fnal.gov/archives/%RED%listname%ENDCOLOR%.html=, where &quot;listname&quot; is the name of mailing list, e.g. [[http://listserv.fnal.gov/archives/osg-sites.html]].

To find out all public lists send email to listserv@fnal.gov with &quot;lists&quot; in the body. 




---++ How to Request a New Mailing List 
 
There is a Request Mailing List Form: http://listserv.opensciencegrid.org/request-list.asp 
Note that the same form is used to request mailing lists for opensciencegrid.org and fnal.gov.
 
The following are steps to follow when creating a mailing list:
   * You will need to provide informations and select the appropriate settings for the list (a brief description of each is provided in the page to enable you to set up the mailing list), among which:
      *	Identify the email address of the primary owner 
      * Provide a name and a brief description of the mailing list. 
      * Include a welcome message for new subscribers 
      * Identify other owners of the list, if applicable
      * Select  =opensciencegrid.org= as _Domain_ for your list, to have a list &quot;@opensciencegrid.org&quot;
   * Include any additional comments in the text area provided. 
   * Submit the form. 



